# Infrastructure Components
- MicroK8s cluster with Traefik and ArgoCD
- Tailscale VPN for remote access
- Cloudflare Tunnel (planned) for internet exposure
- Shared Redis instance for caching and session management
- Ollama for local AI model hosting
- PostgreSQL instance for data storage in shared namespace

# Currently Running Services
These are my following pods at this moment:
- Traefik. Also exposes the traefik dashboard on the home server. 
  - Cluster Port: 8080
  - Traefik Port: 8080
  - Path /dashboard/
  - Namespace: kube-system
- Redis. Shared instance for caching and session management. 
  - Cluster Port: 6379
  - Traefik Port: 6379
  - Namespace: shared
- PostgreSQL. Internal database instance in shared namespace. Accessible at:
  - Cluster Host: postgres.shared.svc.cluster.local
  - Cluster Port: 5432
  - Traefik Host: postgres.home.server
  - Traefik Port: :5432
  - Database: web_crawler
  - User: admin
  - Namespace: shared
  - Currently only has public schema with test table
- ArgoCD, Exposed by traefik. 
  - Cluster Port: 9080
  - Traefik Port: 80
  - Path: /argocd
  - Mamespace: argocd
  - Version: 2.8.4
  - Components:
    - ArgoCD Server (UI and API)
    - ArgoCD Application Controller
    - ArgoCD Repo Server
    - Redis instance for caching (using shared Redis)
    - Authentication is disabled for local development
  - User: admin
- Ollama. Exposed by traefik. 
  - Cluster Port: 9080
  - Traefik Port: 80
  - Path /ollama
  - Namespace: default 
  - Installed models:
    - llama3 (8B model)

  